%N A395005 Numbers k such that k can be expressed as A003418(i)/j where j <= i.
%C A395005 This is A120435 ordered by increasing value with duplicates removed.
%H A395005 Chai Wah Wu, <a href="/A395005/b395005.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a> (terms 1..143 from Zhicheng Wei)
%e A395005 10 is in this sequence because 10 = 60/6 where 60 = A003418(6) and 6<=6.
%o A395005 (PARI) f(n) = lcm(vector(n, i, i)); \\ A003418
%o A395005 isok(k) = my(i=1, fi=f(i)); while (1, for (j=1, i, if (fi/j == k, return(1))); if (fi/i > 2*k, return(0)); i++; fi = f(i);); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 11 2026
